body:
For the last two or three patches i have not been able to buy anything in the client store with IP when the purchase price of the item is higher than the IP amount i had when the patch came through. This means that if a patch comes through when I am at 3000 IP i cant but anything worth more than that until the next patch when i hopefully have more IP then what i had wanted to buy is worth. This wouldnt be so bad if i could say, build up 7800 IP, wait for a patch, then be able to buy anything for the rest of the patch but no. If i spend any ip the top amount of IP i can spend drops with it. 
If i start at 3000 and spend to below 1350 then no matter how much more i gain i cant buy anything worth more than 1350. {{sticker:zombie-brand-facepalm}} 

I've included a picture to illustrate the problem. 

The part that is starting to push me away from this game is that RP is not effected by this. i can purchase and spend as much RP as i like without any issues. I have a problem with this however, i spend enough on skins and the like that id rather earn my champions with IP but with this bug i am essentially FORCED to purchase and champions i want to with RP instead of IP. If this is a bug, it would be great for it to be fixed, if its intentional then you've lost me for good riot. 

-end rant-{{sticker:slayer-jinx-unamused}} 

P.S. Ive seen posts before that switching back to the old client fixes the problem, that would be great if the old client would launch on my machine, which for some unknowable reason it does not.
